The evidence with the title 'Obesity bigger cost for Britain than war and terror | society | The ... ' says Nov 20, 2014  ... Obesity is a greater burden on the UK 's economy than armed violence, war and terrorism , costing the country nearly £ 47bn a year, a report has found.  ... But the country spends about £ 6bn ayear on the medical costs of conditions related to being overweight or obese and a further £ 10 billion on diabetes . 
